    <body>
        <p>A navigation link is a feature that points to additional information from a specific area in a topic or document.</p>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../../Shared/All/Print-Output/Chapter-Discusses-Following.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="D2H-Guides.D2H-Documents-Templates-Content" />
        <MadCap:dropDown MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">Ways to Use Links</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Cross-Reference </span>You can automatically add page references in printed manuals and hyperlinks in online outputs. The page numbers will not appear in online output.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Nav-Links/Cross-References/Inserting-Cross-References.htm">Inserting Cross-References</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Nav-Links/Inserting-Cross-References.htm">Inserting Cross-References</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Expanded, Drop-Down, or Popup Text </span>You can use three different methods to display information that is initially not displayed in your output: Expanded Text, Drop-Down Text, or Popup Text.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Nav-Links/Creating-Expanded-Drop-Down-Popup-Text.htm">Creating Expanded, Drop-Down, or Popup Text</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Nav-Links/Creating-Expanded-Dropdown-or-Popup-Text.htm">Creating Expanded, Drop-Down, or Popup Text</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Expanding/Collapsing Section </span>For online output, you can create sections of content that are expanded or collapsed by default.&#160; This is an ideal way to subdivide a long topic in online documentation.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Nav-Links/Creating-Expanding-Collapsing-Section.htm">Creating an Expanding/Collapsing Section</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Nav-Links/Creating-Expanding-Collapsing-Section.htm">Creating Expanding/Collapsing Sections</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Group </span>Groups can also be referred to as "related topics" or "associative topics" (A-links). When a group of topics is related, a link can be created in your online output that displays a dialog or popup window displaying the list of topics in that group.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Nav-Links/Groups/Groups.htm">About Groups</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Nav-Links/About-Groups.htm">About Groups</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Link </span>You can create links to topics, bookmarks, link tags, keywords, groups, and glossary entries. You can also use drag-and-drop linking to quickly add links from the Word Doc-To-Help Project panel or from a variety of locations in Doc-To-Help.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Nav-Links/Creating-Links.htm">Creating Links</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Nav-Links/Drag-Drop-Linking.htm">Drag-and-Drop Linking</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Nav-Links/Creating-Links.htm">Creating Links</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Nav-Links/Drag-Drop-Linking.htm">Drag-and-Drop Linking</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Link Tag </span>A link tag is a unique identifier for a topic, and makes it possible to create a jump or popup link to a topic.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Nav-Links/Adding-Link-Tag.htm">Adding a Link Tag</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Nav-Links/Adding-Link-Tag.htm">Adding Link Tags</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Related Topics </span>Related topics (also known as "subtopic links") can be created/edited and viewed using the Related Topics pane and the Topics window. The related topics feature is very powerful, because it lets you customize relevant "See Also" links for any topic, without the need to create individual cross-reference links. Combined with the automatically created subtopic relations, this means your online outputs can help your users find the exact topic they need, when they need it. It can also eliminate topic "dead ends" in your online output.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Nav-Links/Managing-Related-Topics.htm">Managing Related Topics</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Nav-Links/Managing-Related-Topics.htm">Managing Related Topics</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
                </ul>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:dropDown MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">note</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #bed230;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">Other features in <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> are also used to add navigation in online output. These features are treated separately in this Help system. They include tables of contents and indexes.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/TOCs/Creating-TOC.htm">Creating a Table of Contents</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Indexes/Indexes.htm">About Indexes</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/TOCs/Creating-TOC.htm">Creating a Table of Contents</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Indexes/About-Indexes-D2H.htm">About Indexes</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
    </body>
</html>